		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=31246#p31246"><![CDATA[
I'm not sure this function is needed, since Lua already has <a href="https://www.lua.org/manual/5.1/manual.html#pdf-string.format">string.format</a>, which does a very similar thing.<br><br>But if I were doing this, I'd try to use the % symbol, since it's the one used in that function. (It's also the symbol used in Python, btw).<br><br>Regarding the name, I'd call it "interpolate", or "parse". I'd not use the __call metamethod.<br><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>string.parse("You have seen this page %{1} times")-- would be more or less equivalent tostring.format("You have seen this page %d times", 1)</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=710">kikito</a> — Mon May 09, 2011 3:56 pm</p><hr />
