		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=30214#p30214"><![CDATA[
Another version of string.insert, which is more consistent in regard to negative indices, at the expense of slightly less elegant code:<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>function string:insert(index, other)  index = (index &lt; 0 and index + 1 or index) % (#self+1)  if index == 1 then    return other .. self  elseif index == 0 then    return self .. other  else    return self:sub(1, index - 1) .. other .. self:sub(index)  endend</code></pre></div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>---------------------| A | B | C | D | E |---------------------1   2   3   4   5   6-6 -5  -4  -3  -2  -1</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=436">Robin</a> — Tue Apr 26, 2011 8:01 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
