		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=30169#p30169"><![CDATA[
Your implementation of string.insert seems a bit... inefficient to me.<br><br>I'd do something like:<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>function string:insert(index, other)  index = index % (#self+1)  if index == 1 then    return other .. self  elseif index == 0 then    return self .. other  else    return self:sub(1, index - 1) .. other .. self:sub(index)  endend</code></pre></div>Didn't test it, but it should work. It handles negative indices as well.<br><br>EDIT: position of insertion<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>---------------------| A | B | C | D | E |---------------------1   2   3   4   5   6-5 -4  -3  -2  -1   0</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=436">Robin</a> — Tue Apr 26, 2011 8:40 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
